It's a concept ğŸ˜…. A school that is not a school.  A museum...which is not a museum.ğŸ˜²  Wander around the establishment with the guide while the students work on their computers or interact.  Quite confusing all the same, we are afraid of annoying or we are even a little embarrassed but if they say that they are used to it ğŸ˜….  Otherwise beautiful works, I'm sharing some photos so as not to spoil everything. Of course not all street art artists are represented - remember that this is the collection of Nicolas Laugero Lasserre - but as an admirer of this art, we learn a lot during the guided tour as well as from from the guide as well as from the visitors (there were experts!!). ğŸ¤©

Atypical place which immerses art in the middle of the rooms of a school. A super original idea that places street art as close as possible to the population. The free guided tour on Thursday evening is super interesting. Only downside: the ambient noise during the guide's explanations.
Friendly guided tour, well commented but the explanations are a little long. We wander from floor to floor among the students.

An unusual place, in which you wander among the students, the computer stations and the street art works. Visits are by reservation but guided by a student volunteer. A must see if you pass through the 17th arrondissement of Paris!
Incredible street art museum with a passionate and exciting guide owner

A very interesting project between school and museum. If you are lucky that your guide is interested in the topic, it is a plus!!! Those who guide are kids from the school themselves. Otherwise the collection is very interesting and rich in artists and references!!! Open Tuesday and Saturday nights. You have to book online and the visit is free (you can help with a tip at the end).
Museum not found and after a few minutes of searching, we ended up learning that it is only open on Tuesdays by reservation... We just wasted time ğŸ¤£ â€¦
A beautiful collection with a very involved guide. On the other hand, the exhibition is -in- the school itself which can sometimes cause some disturbance (it's not a museum atmosphere)
Free entry but go to the website for more information
A very interesting and varied collection of street art. I really enjoyed the guided tour. I recommend!
Very nice place to exhibit street art works among people coming to do computer codingğŸ˜Š... atypical.. â€¦
Very particular but very pleasant study environment. Visits are unfortunately not yet possible during covid
Very good with very interesting guided tour. To do

Superb collection of street art on the grounds of School 42. The mix of genres is very fun. The guided tour is remarkably well organized and the explanations are very interesting. Everything is free upon reservation.

Very original and enriching experience: walk commented by passionate students in the middle of a code school decorated by an impressive collection of street art, which even includes several works created in situ. Well done!

Big disappointment. You will see PHOTOS of street art there. Hosted here and there on the walls of a computer school. The guide undoubtedly knew his subject but his delivery punctuated by a collection of euuuuuuuuhs made him inaudible. We came across another guide who seemed much more efficient. But, in my humble opinion, this 'museum' is absolutely not worth the trip. Prefer a walk to the Butte aux Cailles where street art finds its natural setting: the street.

UNAVOIDABLE.  An incredible collection of street art. If you like street art, you will be served. The school's students take you through the different rooms and inform you about the different works. A real pleasure
I have the chance to study in the school, and seeing all these paintings every day is very nice! Without much knowledge of art, we greatly appreciate the environment!
I loved this visit led by a very knowledgeable student. The works are rich and varied. A must see at all costs.
a great place, a great initiative! student guides who help you experience and share street art as if you were part of one of the crew

Not a museum. ..more of a gallery to present friends...very little or no museum works. ..no old school. ..no ramellzee. ...crash...nasty. from sonic ..from mystic...from futura 2000. ..from nasty...etc...a correct Bansky work without more...shame
Street art exhibition - Duration 1h30 (Guided tour) - Reservation on their website - Possibility of taking photos. Very nice - To discover.
A really cool visit with some really great artists. I really liked it (better to like street art, otherwise forget it)
Great visit! I learned a lot about Street art. And I looked at the walls of Paris differently afterwards
The visits are free and sometimes done with students from the school which is fun. Furthermore, it allows you to discover school 42.
An impressive collection of street art works which stands out in particular for the diversity of the artists presented and the modes of expression.
If you love, or want to know more about street art, this absolutely unique place is not to be missed in Paris!!
In addition to being a museum, we have the pleasure of discovering that it is also a digital school.
Friendly and very nice guide
